These occur once every 28-34 seconds.
The sound effect (which starts with a little bit of silence, so
you'll only get the full warning if you keep pausing) starts playing
1.2 seconds ahead of the flare.

With no shields (including Zoltan shields), 3-6 fires will be started.
Otherwise, 1-2 fires are started. Note the number of shields bubbles doesn't
affect the number of fires, as long as you have at least one.

While there are more fires to start, pick a random room. Then spawn either
1/2 fires (always 1 if there's only one left to spawn), and spawn it into
the room. This uses the normal fire starting mechanics, so if there's
already a fire in that room, it won't always start a new fire - it might
just refill the health of an existing fire.

For each room a fire is started in, there's a 33%/66% chance to deal a
point of damage, depending on whether 1/2 fires were started in that room.
